<P style="page-break-before:always; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:108pt; margin-bottom:12pt; text-indent:36pt; width:504pt; line-height:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">Item 8.01. &nbsp;<U>Other Events</U>.<SUP>1</SUP></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-right:108pt; margin-bottom:12pt; text-indent:36pt; width:504pt; line-height:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>Filed herewith are certain materials (the &#147;Computational Materials&#148;) furnished to the Registrant by Lehman Brothers Inc. (the &#147;Underwriter&#148;) in respect of Structured Asset Investment Loan Trust Mortgage Pass-Through Certificates, Series 2004-11, Class A1, Class A2, Class A3, Class A4, Class M1, Class M2, Class M3, Class M4, Class M5, Class M6, Class M7, Class M8 and Class M9 (the &#147;Publicly-Offered Certificates&#148;). &nbsp;The Publicly-Offered Certificates are being offered pursuant to a Prospectus Supplement dated December 21, 2004, and the related Prospectus dated November 19, 2004 (together, the &#147;Prospectus&#148;), which are being filed with the Commission pursuant to Rule 424(b) under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended (the &#147;Act&#148;). &nbsp;The Publicly-Offered Certificates have been register
ed pursuant to the Act under a Registration Statement on Form S-3 (No. 333-115858) (the &#147;Registration Statement&#148;). &nbsp;The Computational Materials are incorporated by reference in the Registration Statement.</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-right:108pt; margin-bottom:12pt; text-indent:36pt; width:504pt; line-height:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The Computational Materials were prepared solely by the Underwriter and the Registrant did not prepare or participate (other than providing the background information concerning the underlying pool of assets upon which the Computational Materials are based to the Underwriter) in the preparation of the Computational Materials.</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-right:108pt; margin-bottom:12pt; text-indent:36pt; width:504pt; line-height:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>Any statements or information contained in the Computational Materials shall be deemed to be modified or superseded for purposes of the Prospectus and the Registration Statement by statements or information contained in the Prospectus.</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-right:108pt; margin-bottom:0pt; width:504pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt"><BR></P>

<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:18pt; padding-right:-18pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">(1)</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:18pt; padding-right:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">The Certificates were priced assuming 100% of the Prepayment Assumption. &nbsp;100% of the Prepayment Assumption assumes 28% CPR for the Adjustable Rate Mortgage Loans and 23% CPR for the Fixed Rate Mortgage Loans.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">(2)</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">Initial Credit Enhancement includes overcollateralization of approximately 0.50%.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">(3)</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">The Class A1 and A2 Certificates and the A4(1) Component are the Senior Certificates of Group 1.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">(4)</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">The Class A3 Certificates and the A4(2) Component are the Senior Certificates of Group 2.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">(5)</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">The Class A4 Certificate is made up of two Components, one from each Collateral Group. &nbsp;The A4(1) Component balance and A4(2) Component balance is approximately $486,013,000 and $123,375,000, respectively.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:-18pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><BR></P>
<HR style="padding-top:7.2pt; padding-bottom:7.2pt">
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt"><B>Principal Payment Priority</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">On each Payment Date, principal in the amount of any Net Swap Payment or swap termination payment due to the Swap Provider and remaining unpaid (after application of interest received or advanced for this purpose on such Payment Date), will be deposited into the swap account and paid as described in the Swap Account Payment Priority, to be paid from each of Group 1 and Group 2 in proportion to the aggregate collateral balance of each group. &nbsp;Any funds remaining will be paid in the following order of priority: </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">I.</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; text-indent:18pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">Prior to the Stepdown Date, or whenever a Trigger Event is in effect:</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:108pt; text-indent:-90pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">1)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:108pt; text-indent:-31.5pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">A)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; padding-left:108pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">All principal from Group 1 will be paid to the Class A1 and Class A2 Certificates and the A4(1) Component, sequentially and in that order, until they have been reduced to zero; and</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:108pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">B)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; padding-left:108pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">All principal from Group 2 will be paid to the Class A3 Certificates and the A4(2) Component, sequentially and in that order, until they have been reduced to zero; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:72pt; text-indent:-54pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">2)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; padding-left:72pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">If the Senior Certificates related to either group have been retired, all principal from that group will be allocated to the Senior Certificates of the unrelated group, to be paid as described above, until all the Senior Certificates have been reduced to zero; and</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:72pt; text-indent:-54pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">3)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; padding-left:72pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">All remaining principal will be allocated to the Class M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7, M8, M9 and B Certificates, sequentially and in that order, until reduced to zero.</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">II.</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; text-indent:18pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">On or after the Stepdown Date and as long as a Trigger Event is not in effect: </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:72pt; text-indent:-54pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">1)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; padding-left:72pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">All principal from each Group will be allocated to the related Senior Certificates, to be paid as described in (I)(1) above, provided, however, that principal will only be allocated to the Senior Certificates in the amount required to achieve the Targeted Senior Enhancement Percentage in the aggregate;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:72pt; text-indent:-54pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">2)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; padding-left:72pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">If the Senior Certificates related to either group have been retired, all principal from that group will be allocated to the Senior Certificates of the unrelated group, to be paid as described above, until the Targeted Senior Enhancement Percentage has been reached in the aggregate; and</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:72pt; text-indent:-54pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">3)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; padding-left:72pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">All remaining principal will be allocated to the Class M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7, M8, M9 and B Certificates, sequentially and in that order, until the Credit Enhancement behind each class is equal to two times the related Initial Enhancement Percentage. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The Stepdown Date is the later of (i) the Distribution Date upon which the original Senior Enhancement Percentage (as defined herein) doubles to meet the Targeted Senior Enhancement Percentage of 27.00%, or (ii) the 37<SUP>th</SUP> distribution date.</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt"><BR></P>
<HR style="padding-top:7.2pt; padding-bottom:7.2pt">
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:5.85pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt"><B>Interest Payment Priority</B> </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The Interest Rates for the Class A1, A2, A3, A4, &nbsp;M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7 and M8 Certificates &nbsp;(the &#147;LIBOR Certificates&#148;) will be equal to the lesser of (i) one-month LIBOR plus their respective margins and (ii) their Net Funds Cap (as defined herein). &nbsp;Interest for the LIBOR Certificates will be calculated on an actual/360 basis.</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The Interest Rate on the Class M9 and B Certificates will be equal to the lesser of (i) 5.00% and (ii) the Net Funds Cap. &nbsp;Interest for the Class M9 and B Certificates will be calculated on a 30/360 basis. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The &#147;Accrual Period&#148; for the LIBOR Certificates and the Class M9 and B Certificates for each Distribution Date will be the one-month period beginning on the immediately preceding Distribution Date (or on December 25, 2004, in the case of the first Accrual Period) and ending on the day immediately preceding the related Distribution Date.</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">Interest received or advanced on each Distribution Date will be allocated in the following priority:</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(1)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay fees: Servicing Fee, Securities Administrator Fee and Mortgage Insurance Fee;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(2)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To deposit into the Swap Account (as defined below) any Net Swap Payment (as defined below) or any swap termination payment owed to the Swap Provider pursuant to the swap agreement, to be paid from each of Group 1 and Group 2 Interest in an amount proportionate to their loan balance; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(3)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay Current Interest and Carryforward Interest to the Class A1 and Class A2 Certificates and the A4(1) Component from Group 1 Interest on a pro rata basis;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(4)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay Current Interest and Carryforward Interest to the Class A3 Certificates and the A4(2) Component from Group 2 Interest on a pro rata basis; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(5)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay Current Interest and Carryforward Interest to the Senior Certificates on a pro rata basis to the extent not paid above;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(6)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay Current Interest and Carryforward Interest to the Class M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7, M8, M9 and B Certificates, sequentially and in that order;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(7)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:18pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay the Credit Risk Manager Fee;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(8)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay to the Trustee previously unreimbursed extraordinary costs, liabilities and expenses, to the extent provided in the Trust Agreement;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(9)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">Any interest remaining after the application of (1) through (8) above will be deemed excess interest for such Distribution Date and will be distributed as principal, according to the principal distribution rule in effect for such Payment Date, as needed to maintain the Overcollateralization Target;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(10)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay concurrently in proportion to their respective Basis Risk Shortfall and Unpaid Basis Risk Shortfall amounts after giving effect to distributions already made on such Distribution Date, to the Class A1, A2, A3 and A4 Certificates, any Basis Risk Shortfall and Unpaid Basis Risk Shortfall amounts;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(11)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay sequentially to the Class M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7, M8, M9 and B Certificates any Basis Risk Shortfall and Unpaid Basis Risk Shortfall amounts; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:27pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(12)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.15pt; padding-left:27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay sequentially to the Class M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7, M8, M9 and B Certificates any Deferred Amounts; and</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(13)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:4.6pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:9pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay remaining amounts to the holder of the Class X Certificate. </P>
<HR style="padding-top:7.2pt; padding-bottom:7.2pt">
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt" align=justify><B>Interest Rate Swap Agreement</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-right:7.9pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The 59-month Interest Rate Swap Agreement (the &#147;Swap Agreement&#148;) will obligate the Trust to pay a predetermined annual rate (as shown below) on the swap notional amount in each period. &nbsp;The Trust will receive payments equal to an annual rate of one-month LIBOR on the swap notional amount for each period over the life of the Swap Agreement. &nbsp;The payments will be netted against each other each month (the &#147;Net Swap Payment&#148;) and will be deposited into an account (the &#147;Swap Account&#148;).</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>

<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<HR style="padding-top:7.2pt; padding-bottom:7.2pt">
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt" align=justify><B>Swap Account Payment Priority</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">All payments due under the Swap Agreement and any swap termination payment pursuant to the Swap Agreement will be deposited into the Swap Account, and allocated in the following order of priority:</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(1)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:2.75pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay any Net Swap Payment owed to the Swap Counterparty pursuant to the Swap Agreement; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(2)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:2.75pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay any swap termination payment to the Swap Counterparty, to the extent the termination is not due to a default on the part of the Swap Counterparty; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(3)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:2.75pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To the Class A1, A2, A3 and A4 Certificates, Current Interest and Carryforward Interest, on a <I>pro rata</I> basis, to the extent not yet paid; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(4)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:2.75pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To the Class M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7, M8, M9 and B Certificates, Current Interest and Carryforward Interest, sequentially and in that order, to the extend not yet paid; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(5)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:2.75pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To be paid as principal, in accordance with the principal distribution rules in effect for such Distribution Date, as needed to maintain the Overcollateralization Target; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(6)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:2.75pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay concurrently in proportion to their respective Basis Risk Shortfall and Unpaid Basis Risk Shortfall amounts after giving effect to distributions already made on such Distribution Date, to the Class A1, A2, A3 and A4 Certificates, any Basis Risk Shortfall and Unpaid Basis Risk Shortfall amounts;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(7)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:2.75pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To the Class M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7, M8, M9 and B Certificates, any Basis Risk Shortfall and Unpaid Basis Risk Shortfall amounts, sequentially and in that order; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(8)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay sequentially to the Class M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7, M8, M9 and B Certificates any Deferred Amounts; </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(9)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">To pay any swap termination payment to the Swap Counterparty, to the extent the termination is due to a default on the part of the Swap Counterparty; and</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-27pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">(10)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">All remaining amounts to the holder of the Class X Certificate. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt"><B>Carryforward Interest</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">&#147;Carryforward Interest&#148; for each Class of LIBOR Certificates and the Class M9 and B Certificates for any Distribution Date will be the sum of (1) the amount, if any, by which (x) the sum of (A) Current Interest for such Class for the immediately preceding Distribution Date and (B) any unpaid Carryforward Interest from previous Distribution Dates exceeds (y) the amount distributed in respect of interest on such Class on such immediately preceding Distribution Date, and (2) interest on such amount for the related Accrual Period at the applicable Interest Rate. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<HR style="padding-top:7.2pt; padding-bottom:7.2pt">
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;Current Interest&#148; for any Class of LIBOR Certificates or the Class M9 and B Certificates for any Distribution Date will be the aggregate amount of interest accrued at the applicable Interest Rate during the related Accrual Period on the Class Principal Amount of that Class.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt"><B>Net Funds Cap</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The &#147;Senior Net Funds Cap&#148; for each Distribution Date and each Group will be the annual rate equal to (a) a fraction, expressed as a percentage, the numerator of which is the product of (1) the related Optimal Interest Remittance Amount (as defined below) for such date and (2) 12, and the denominator of which is the related Group balance for the immediately preceding Distribution Date, multiplied by (b) a fraction, the numerator of which is 30 and the denominator of which is the actual number of days in the accrual period, provided that with respect to the Class M9 and B Certificates clause (b) will be set equal to 1. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The &#147;Subordinate Net Funds Cap&#148; for any Distribution Date will be the weighted average of the Senior Net Funds Caps for the two groups, weighted on the basis of their Group Subordinate Amounts; provided, however, on any Distribution Date after the Senior Certificates related to either Group has been reduced to zero, such weighting shall be on the basis of the principal balance of each Group.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The &#147;Optimal Interest Remittance Amount&#148; with respect to each Distribution Date and each Group will be equal to the amount, if any, by which (1) the product of (A) (x) the weighted average of the Net Mortgage Rates (as defined below) of the Mortgage Loans in the Group, as of the first day of the related collection period divided by (y) 12 and (B) the aggregate Group balance for the immediately preceding Distribution Date exceeds (2) the proportionate share of any Net Swap Payment due to the Swap Counterparty. </P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The &#147;Net Mortgage Rate&#148; with respect to any Mortgage Loan will be the Mortgage Rate thereof reduced by the sum of the Servicing Fee Rate, the Securities Administrator Fee Rate and, in the case of an Insured Mortgage Loan, the Mortgage Insurance Fee Rate.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt"><B>Origination and Servicing</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The majority of the Mortgage Loans were originated by Option One (41.57%), BNC (36.76%), Finance America (7.66%), and ALS (5.64%) and as of the Closing Date were initially serviced by Option One (78.30%), Ocwen (7.79%), Chase (5.96%), Aurora (5.68%) and Wells Fargo (2.26%). &nbsp;Approximately 46.91% of the loans serviced by Option One (representing approximately 36.74% of the aggregate population) are expected to transfer to another servicer in the securitization on February 1, 2005.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman Bold; font-size:14pt"><B>Mortgage Insurance</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">Approximately 69.03% of the first lien Mortgage Loans with over 80% Loan-to-Value (&#147;LTV&#148;) will be covered by a loan level primary mortgage insurance policy provided by Radian or certain other providers. &nbsp;This coverage will generally reduce the LTV of the insured loans to 60%.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt"><B>Credit Risk Manager</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The MurrayHill Company (&#147;MurrayHill&#148;) will act as a credit risk manager on behalf of the Trust. &nbsp;MurrayHill&#8217;s primary function will be to monitor and advise the servicers with respect to default management and reporting for the benefit of the Trust. The following summarizes some of MurrayHill&#8217;s monthly activities: </P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-12pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:-18pt; font-family:Symbol">&#183;</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:18pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Symbol"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Monitoring of all loans that are 60 or more days delinquent to ensure all foreclosure timelines are met or forbearance plans are established. </FONT></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-12pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:-18pt; font-family:Symbol">&#183;</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:18pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Symbol"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Monitoring of the servicers&#8217; claim process for loans with mortgage insurance to ensure insurance claims are filed in an accurate and timely way.</FONT></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-12pt; padding-left:18pt; text-indent:-18pt; font-family:Symbol">&#183;</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:18pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Symbol"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Review of the prepayment penalty collections by the servicers.</FONT></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<HR style="padding-top:7.2pt; padding-bottom:7.2pt">
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt" align=justify><B>Basis Risk Shortfall</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">With respect to each Distribution Date, to the extent that (a) the amount of interest payable to a Class, as calculated without regard to the applicable Net Funds Cap, exceeds (b) the amount calculated at the stated rate (such excess, a &#147;Basis Risk Shortfall&#148;), that Class will be entitled to the amount of such Basis Risk Shortfall or Unpaid Basis Risk Shortfall, plus interest thereon at the applicable Interest Rate, before the Class X and Class R Certificates are entitled to any distributions. &nbsp;The &#147;Unpaid Basis Risk Shortfall&#148; for any Class of Certificates on any Distribution Date will be the aggregate of all Basis Risk Shortfalls for such Class for all previous Distribution Dates, together with interest thereon at the applicable Interest Rate, less all payments made with respect to such Class in respect of such Basis Risk Shortfalls on or prior to such Distribution Date.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt" align=justify><B>Losses</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">Losses that are not covered by mortgage insurance are allocated in the following order: excess spread, overcollateralization, the Class B Certificates, and to the Class M Certificates in inverse order of priority. &nbsp;The allocation of losses to a class will result in a writedown of its principal amount and is referred to as an &#147;Applied Loss Amount&#148;. &nbsp;The balance of the Class A1, A2, A3 and A4 Certificates will not be reduced by allocation of Applied Loss Amounts.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt"><B>Deferred Amount &amp; Subsequent Recoveries</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">With respect to each Distribution Date, the &#147;Deferred Amount&#148; for each Class of Class M Certificates and Class B Certificates will be equal to the amount by which (x) the aggregate of Applied Loss Amounts previously applied in reduction of the Class Principal Amount thereof exceeds (y) the sum of (i) the aggregate of amounts previously distributed in reimbursement thereof and (ii) the amount by which the Principal Amount of such class has been increased due to Subsequent Recoveries. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">A &#147;Subsequent Recovery&#148; is an amount recovered with respect to a Mortgage Loan after it has been liquidated and the loss has been passed through to the Trust. &nbsp;Subsequent Recoveries will increase the principal amount of classes which have been allocated an Applied Loss Amount, in order of seniority, by an amount equal to the lesser of (i) the outstanding Deferred Amount for such class and (ii) the amount of Subsequent Recoveries available after application to more senior classes. &nbsp;Funds related to Subsequent Recoveries will be included in the remittance amount for the related Distribution Date.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt"><B>10% Optional Redemption</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The transaction can be called by the Master Servicer, Aurora Loan Services (an affiliate of Lehman Brothers), on any Distribution Date following the month in which the loan principal balance of the Mortgage Loans is reduced to less than 10% of the Cut-off Date loan principal balance. &nbsp;If the optional redemption is not exercised on the first Distribution Date on which it is able to be exercised, beginning with the next succeeding Distribution Date, the margins on the Class A1, A2, A3 and A4 Certificates will double, the margins on the Class M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7 and M8 Certificates will increase to 1.5 times their initial margins and the stated rate on the Class M9 and B Certificates will increase to 5.50%. </P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<HR style="padding-top:7.2pt; padding-bottom:7.2pt">
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt"><B>Credit Enhancement</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt"><B>Subordination</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">Classes A1, A2, A3 and A4 will have limited protection by means of the subordination of the Class B Certificates and the Class M Certificates. &nbsp;Classes A1, A2, A3 and A4 will have the preferential right to receive interest due to them and principal available for distribution over Classes having a lower priority of distribution. &nbsp;Similarly, each Class of Class M Certificates will be senior to all other Classes of Class M Certificates with a higher numerical designation and to the Class B Certificates. &nbsp;If on any Distribution Date after giving effect to all realized losses and distributions of principal on such Distribution Date, the aggregate Certificate Principal Amount exceeds the aggregate loan balance, the Class B Certificates and Class M Certificates will be reduced by the Applied Loss Amount in the following order: to the Class B Certificates, until reduced to zero; then to the Class M Certificates in inv
erse order of priority, until all the Class M Certificates have been reduced to zero.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt"><B>Overcollateralization</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">Excess interest may be used to pay down the Certificates so the aggregate loan balance exceeds the aggregate certificate balance (Overcollateralization or &#147;OC&#148;). &nbsp;Excess interest will be used to maintain the OC Target.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The &#147;OC Target&#148; will not step down. &nbsp;The OC Target with respect to any Distribution Date is equal to the initial OC, or approximately 0.50% of the Cut-off Date collateral balance. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt"><B>Trigger Events</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">A &#147;Trigger Event&#148; will have occurred with respect to any Distribution Date if the Rolling Three Month Delinquency Rate as of the last day of the immediately preceding month equals or exceeds 55.00% of the Senior Enhancement Percentage for that Distribution Date, or if the Cumulative Realized Losses exceed:</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt"><B><U>Distribution Date </U></B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; text-indent:198pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt"><B><U>Loss Percentage</U></B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">January 2008 to December 2008 </P>
<P style="margin:0pt; text-indent:198pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">2.00% for the first month, plus an additional 1/12th of 1.25% </P>
<P style="margin:0pt; text-indent:198pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">for each month thereafter</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">January 2009 to December 2009 </P>
<P style="margin:0pt; text-indent:198pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">3.25% for the first month, plus an additional 1/12th of</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:180pt; text-indent:18pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">1.00% for each month thereafter</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">January 2010 to December 2010 </P>
<P style="margin:0pt; text-indent:198pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">4.25% for the first month, plus an additional 1/12th of</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:180pt; text-indent:18pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">0.35% for each month thereafter</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-13pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">January 2011 and thereafter </P>
<P style="margin:0pt; text-indent:198pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">4.60%</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt"><B>Trigger Events (continued)</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The &#147;Rolling Three Month Delinquency Rate&#148; with respect to any Distribution Date will be the average of the Delinquency Rates for each of the three (or one and two, in the case of the first and second Distribution Dates) immediately preceding months.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The &#147;Delinquency Rate&#148; for any month will be the fraction, expressed as a percentage, the numerator of which is the aggregate outstanding principal balance of all Mortgage Loans 60 or more days delinquent (including all foreclosures and REO Properties) as of the close of business on the last day of such month, and the denominator of which is the aggregate loan balance as of the close of business on the last day of such month.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">&#147;Cumulative Realized Losses&#148; with respect to any Distribution Date will be equal to the fraction, expressed as a percentage, obtained by dividing (x) the aggregate amount of cumulative Realized Losses incurred on the Mortgage Loans from the Cut-off Date through the last day of the related Collection Period by (y) the Cut-off Date Balance.</P>
<HR style="padding-top:7.2pt; padding-bottom:7.2pt">
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The &#147;Senior Enhancement Percentage&#148; for any Distribution Date will be the fraction, expressed as a percentage, the numerator of which is the sum of the total Certificate Principal Amount of the Class B Certificates, the Class M Certificates and the Overcollateralization Amount (which, for purposes of this definition only, will not be less than zero), and the denominator of which is the aggregate loan balance, after giving effect to distributions on that Distribution Date.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>

The remaining approximately 41.57% of the Mortgage Loans have a servicing fee equal to 0.30% annually for the first 10 Distribution Dates, 0.40% for Distribution Dates 11 through 30, and 0.65% thereafter.</P>

<TR><TD style="padding-left:7.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:7.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt; border-left:0.5pt solid #000000" valign=top width=173.933><P style="margin-top:2.5pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Clearing/Registration:</P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:7.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:7.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt; border-right:0.5pt solid #000000" valign=top width=450.067><P style="margin-top:2.5pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Book-entry through DTC, Euroclear, and Cedel</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:7.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:7.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt; border-left:0.5pt solid #000000" valign=top width=173.933><P style="margin-top:2.5pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Denomination:</P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:7.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:7.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt; border-right:0.5pt solid #000000" valign=top width=450.067><P style="margin-top:2.5pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Minimum $25,000; increments $1 in excess thereof for Classes A1, A2, A3 and A4. &nbsp;Minimum $100,000; increments $1 in excess thereof for the Class M Certificates and Class B Certificates.</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:7.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:7.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt; border-left:0.5pt solid #000000" valign=top width=173.933><P style="margin-top:2.5pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">SMMEA Eligibility:</P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:7.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:7.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt; border-right:0.5pt solid #000000" valign=top width=450.067><P style="margin-top:2.5pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">None of the classes are expected to be SMMEA eligible</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:7.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:7.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt; border-left:0.5pt solid #000000" valign=top width=173.933><P style="margin-top:2.5pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">ERISA Eligibility:</P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:7.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:7.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt; border-right:0.5pt solid #000000" valign=top width=450.067><P style="margin-top:2.5pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Class A and Class M Certificates are expected to be ERISA eligible</P>
</TD></TR>

<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><B>(1)</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><B>Based on one-month LIBOR and six-month LIBOR of 20% for each period. &nbsp;</B></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:36pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><B>(2)</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:36pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><B>Assumes 100% of the Prepayment Assumption as defined on page 2. </B></P>

<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; text-indent:18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><B>(1)</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><B>Based on gradually increasing one-month LIBOR, six-month LIBOR, and one-year CMT.</B></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; text-indent:18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><B>(2)</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><B>Assumes 100% of the Prepayment Assumption as defined on page 2. </B></P>
<P style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; text-indent:18pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><B>(3)</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt"><B>Does not include swap payments to the Trust, reflects swap payments made by the Trust.</B></P>
<HR style="padding-top:7.2pt; padding-bottom:7.2pt">
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:16pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14pt"><B>Breakeven CDR Table</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; line-height:13pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:11pt">The table below displays the Constant Default Rate (&#147;CDR&#148;) and the related cumulative collateral loss wherein the Class will first incur a writedown. Calculations are run to maturity at the forward one-month LIBOR, six-month LIBOR, and one-year CMT curves. Other assumptions incorporated include: (1) 100% of the Prepayment Assumption, (2) 40% loss severity, (3) 6 month lag from default to loss, (4) principal and interest advanced during the 6 month lag and (5) triggers fail (i.e., no stepdown).</P>
